            "description": "For my Bachelor's thesis, I researched Pollard's Rho algorithm for solving Discrete Logarithm problems. These problems have a great importance in Cryptography, and the subject has a very mathematical background, making it a suitable subject for my Mathematics Bachelor's thesis.\nI ended up implementing Pollard's Rho algorithm on the GPU, in a way that accelerated the algorithm linearly in the number of threads used. Using a GPU, this meant a great improvement over the regular algorithm.\nThe thesis (in dutch) can be found here: https://dspace.library.uu.nl/handle/1874/382168",
