        {
            "title": "Simulationlibraries for the Dutch Railways (NS)",
            "date": {
                "start": {
                    "month": 2,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2019
                },
                "end": {
                    "month": 6,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2019
                }
            },
            "description": "For my final project for the Computer Science bachelor, myself and 10 others have made a number of Python libraries for the Dutch Railways (NS), that they will use in their research into AI. The NS wants to use machine learning for the online-planning of their shunting yards, to better handle disturbances as they happen.\nThe main library is meant to give the possible actions one can take, given the current situation. It has a businessrule validator, to check if a state satisfies all constraints. Which constraints are used can be easily configured by the researchers. Also, the library lets the reasearchers create their own rules for maximum extensibility.\nThe other libraries are meant for seeing how robust a planning is, and for making the libraries available in other languages through gRPC.",
